OL,6,FHe continued: "Since this tragedy, we
OL,7,Fhave continued to transform the safety
OL,8,Fof our workforce through the
OL,9,Fdevelopment of new technology and
OL,10,Fplanning tools, which have almost
OL,11,Fentirely eliminated the need to work
OL,12,Fon the railway when trains are running.
OL,14,F"Today's judgment reinforces why
OL,15,Fsafety must always be our first
OL,16,Fconsideration, and we will continue to
OL,17,Fdo all we can to make our railways the
OL,18,Fsafest they can be."
